<h1>Orecchiette with Broccoli Rabe</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>3 plant-based Italian sausage</li>
  <li>1 1/2 bunches broccoli rabe</li>
  <li>8 ounces dry orecchiette</li>
  <li>4 cloves garlic, sliced</li>
  <li>1/4 cup dry white wine</li>
  <li>1 tablespoon lemon juice</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon lemon zest</li>
  <li>1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes</li>
  <li>2 onions, caramelized</li>
  <li>8 sun-dried tomatoes, chopped</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Heat a cast-iron skillet over medium heat.</li>
  <li>Cook sausage, breaking into small pieces, until well-browned, about 2 minutes. Remove and set aside.</li>
  <li>Prepare a large pot of salted boiling water (it will be used for the pasta, too).</li>
  <li>Drop the broccoli rabe into the boiling water and boil for 2 minutes.</li>
  <li>Scoop out the broccoli rabe, reserving the boiling water.</li>
  <li>Drain and pat dry the broccoli rabe, then chop into 1-inch pieces.</li>
  <li>Bring the pot of water back to a boil and cook the pasta until al dente, reserving 1/2 cup of the pasta water.</li>
  <li>Heat a large skillet over medium heat.</li>
  <li>Add the garlic and broccoli rabe and cook for 30 seconds.</li>
  <li>Add the wine, cook for 30 seconds, then add the pasta.</li>
  <li>Add the reserved pasta water, lemon juice, lemon zest, red pepper flakes, and salt and pepper to taste.</li>
  <li>Stir in the cooked sausage, caramelized onions, and sun-dried tomatoes.</li>
</ol>
